headline: Lilly's baricitinib delivered near-complete scalp hair regrowth at one year for adolescents with severe alopecia areata in Phase 3 BRAVE-AA-PEDS trial
summary: New results from Eli Lilly and Company (NYSE: LLY) and Incyte (NASDAQ: INCY) showed once-daily, oral baricitinib 4 mg helped the majority of adolescent patients (ages 12 to <18) with severe alopecia areata (AA) achieve successful hair regrowth on the scalp, eyebrows and eyelashes at one year. These 52-week results from the BRAVE-AA-PEDS trial – the largest Phase 3 study of its kind – will be presented at the 2025 Fall Clinical Dermatology (FCD) Conference, taking place Oct. 23-26 in Las Vegas.1
